In Russia, there will be two new areas of pre-social and economic development, Abaza and Novotroitsk.
The relevant regulations of the RF Government will enter into force today, 4 August.
The boundaries and economic activities of the TAR in the territory of the city of Abaza in the Republic of Hakasia have been defined.
The city with 15,000 people will have a special legal business regime, as well as a minimum resident capital investment, and a minimum number of new permanent jobs.
This is expected to attract some 2.5 billion roubles to the city, and more than 600 new jobs will be created.
The list of economic activities in which a special legal regime of business will be applied in the Abasa. For example, plantation, animal husbandry, food production, non-alcoholic beverages and clothing will be included in the list of economic activities.
