There, the city of Novotroitsk will also establish an area pre-social and economic development.
This will allow the diversification of the monocarbon economy, reduce its dependence on the grading company Ural Steel, and create more than 2.3 thousand jobs and attract investments of more than 8 billion roubles.
The list of economic activities in which the new TOR will have a special legal regime for entrepreneurs includes, inter alia, freshwater fishing, feed production, medicines and medical supplies.
Novotroitsk became the first of the Orenburg region monorodes to become a TOR.
